  <h1>Statistician on a Plane Joke</h1>
  <time datetime=2014-02-27T17:41:52Z class="post-date">Thu, Feb 27, 2014</time>
  <blockquote>
<p>Speaking of probability and statistics, there is the story of a statistician who told a friend that he never took airplanes: &#8220;I have computed the probability that there will be a bomb on the plane,&#8221; he explained, &#8220;and although this probability is low, it is still too high for my comfort. &#8221; Two weeks later, the friend met the statistician on a plane. &#8220;How come you changed your theory?&#8221; he asked. &#8220;Oh, I didn&#8217;t change my theory; it&#8217;s just that I subsequently computed the probability that there would simultaneously be two bombs on a plane. This probability is low enough for my comfort. So now I simply carry my own bomb.&#8221;</p>

